Error Handling Standards
HTTP Status Codes
Range	Category	Description
2xx	Success	Request succeeded
4xx	Client Error	Request invalid or unauthorized
5xx	Server Error	Internal server error
Standard Error Response Format
json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "string",
    "message": "string (human readable)",
    "details": "string | null",
    "timestamp": "2026-05-12T10:00:00Z",
    "request_id": "string (correlation ID)",
    "path": "/api/manager/team"
  }
}
Error Codes
HTTP Status	Error Code	Description	Client Action
400	VALIDATION_ERROR	Request validation failed	Check request body
400	MISSING_FIELD	Required field missing	Add missing field
401	UNAUTHORIZED	No or invalid token	Redirect to login
403	FORBIDDEN	Insufficient permissions	Show permission error
404	NOT_FOUND	Resource not found	Verify resource ID
409	CONFLICT	Resource version mismatch	Refresh and retry
429	RATE_LIMITED	Too many requests	Wait and retry (check Retry-After header)
500	INTERNAL_ERROR	Server error	Retry with backoff
503	SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE	Integration service down	Try later
Rate Limiting
Tier	Requests per Minute	Requests per Hour
Default (authenticated)	60	1000
Employee endpoints	120	2000
Admin/HR endpoints	30	500
Webhooks	300	5000
